<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Balanced Classes? MY @$$...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Landros the Shadowstalker">Landros the Shadowstalker</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:27 p.m. 5/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Balanced Classes? MY @$$...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>First thing first there is no such thing as a balanced class. Wizards Enchanters and Druids are PVP gods!!! While warriors, rogues, and magicians are at the bottom of the food chain. All others are somewhere in the middle. Evidence of this is the mass creation of druids and enchanters. I took my own little private poll and 17% of all new players on the pvp servers are druids. Another 12% are enchanters. Now go on a non pvp server and only 2% are enchanters and 12% druids. What the hell is that. I can admit that there are also alot of warriors but that doesnt make up for the lack of rogues. I counted 3 rogues, lower than level 8, on the entire pvp server. I don't even want to talk about magicians and how unbalanced they are...What the hell is the point of summoning arrows if you cant use them? To give them to a ranger who will later probably end up killing you?

<P>Now I want to know if eq will ever be made more balanced than it is? Dont tell me this is the grass is always greener syndrome cause i have level 25 rogue 27 enchanter and 30 magician. out of all of these my enchanter is most deadly. My magician cant even take on a level 26 druid!!!!! Is anyone else with me on this.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
